invariant concurrent_futures_extra194.cf_Future_add_done_callback_qualname_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__.__eq__('Future.add_done_callback') returns True — Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__=='Future.add_done_callback' (len=24: 'Future'=6+'.'=1+'add_done_callback'=17=24); add_done_callback(fn) registers fn to be called with the Future object as its only argument when the future is cancelled or finishes running; callbacks are called in the thread that called cancel() or in the thread/process that completed the work; Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__ (24) is the longest qualname in this spec; Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__ (24) > Future.exception.__qualname__ (16) by 8; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
